tasks.prompt:
Read AGENTS.md first. Then do the following:

1. Initialize a Next.js 15 project in the repo root with: TypeScript, Tailwind CSS 3.4, App Router, no src/ dir, import alias @/*. Run: npx create-next-app@latest . --typescript --tailwind --app --src-dir=false --import-alias='@/*' --no-git

2. Install dependencies: npm install framer-motion lucide-react

3. Create app/layout.tsx — minimal root layout, no global fonts, just Tailwind base:
```tsx
import type { Metadata } from 'next'
import './globals.css'
export const metadata: Metadata = { title: 'oh-my-design', description: '32 design style landing pages' }
export default function RootLayout({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
  return <html lang="en"><body>{children}</body></html>
}
```

4. Create app/globals.css with just Tailwind directives:
```css
@tailwind base;
@tailwind components;
@tailwind utilities;
```

5. Create app/page.tsx — the gallery home page. It imports STYLES from lib/styles-registry.ts and renders a grid of cards. Each card shows: style name, category badge, vibe text, accent color swatch, and a link to /styles/[slug]. Use a clean, neutral design (white background, slate colors). Mark built styles with a green dot, unbuilt with gray. Add a header with the title 'oh-my-design' and subtitle '32 design style showcases'.

6. Update tailwind.config.ts to include content: ['./app/**/*.{ts,tsx}', './lib/**/*.{ts,tsx}'] and add fadeIn/slideUp keyframes.

7. Create next.config.ts:
```ts
import type { NextConfig } from 'next'
const nextConfig: NextConfig = {}
export default nextConfig
```

8. Verify the project builds: npm run build

Do NOT modify designprompts_dev_all_styles.md, AGENTS.md, docs/, or lib/styles-registry.ts — those already exist.
